{"TopicId":84938,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[1.0.5] Camera Tools v1.5.1 (\u002Bdogfight mode, autozoom margin slider) - March 28","CreatedByName":"BahamutoD","CreatedById":72433,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-09-19T01:13:29Z","PageNum":11,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"allmhuran","CreatedById":66124,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-05T05:56:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just tried the new release of this, thanks for keeping it going.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nPath mode seems to have an issue if you save a path and then want to use it again when reloading the kerbal save file. I had a path going around the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E, but when I reloaded the game the first point of the path was in a different position and pointing up at the sky. Might be to do with the rotation of kerbin or its orbit around the sun? It seems like the path tool needs to store its reference frame.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"BarryDennen12","CreatedById":50869,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-07T16:51:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI feel a bit of a dunce for asking, but did the doppler effect get broken again at any stage? I\u0027m trying the aforementioned \u0027caretaker\u0027 release and it doesn\u0027t seem to work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-02-07T16:51:45Z\u0022 title=\u002202/07/2017 04:51  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 7, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by BarryDennen12\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Azimech","CreatedById":50750,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-07T20:19:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222947799\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002284938\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221486486286\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002250869\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022BarryDennen12\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, BarryDennen12 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI feel a bit of a dunce for asking, but did the doppler effect get broken again at any stage? I\u0027m trying the aforementioned \u0027caretaker\u0027 release and it doesn\u0027t seem to work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, when KSP 1.1 arrived. AFAIK hasn\u0027t worked since. Should be easy to fix because the feature is embedded in Unity. But I\u0027m no programmer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"BarryDennen12","CreatedById":50869,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-11T16:47:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBummer! Not a deal breaker by any stretch, but it\u0027s a lovely little touch when it is working.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Servo","CreatedById":149419,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-15T03:05:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00221410527\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002284938\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221411089209\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002272433\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022BahamutoD\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/18/2014 at 9:13 PM, BahamutoD said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n- Keys:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n8: forward\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n5: backward\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n4: left\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n6: right\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n7: up\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1: down\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n9: zoom in\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3: zoom out\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m a bit confused as to how the pathing mode works. Could somebody clarify that for me?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAwesome mod! Even from what I know how to use, I love it!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jebs_SY","CreatedById":169510,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-20T13:23:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/99277-wren/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002299277\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/99277-wren/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Wren\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0or @ any care taker...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow is your mood for modding at the moment? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nI have a small issue, that is at the same time a deal breaker for me. Using KSP 1.22 and the latest CT version.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs soon as I use a camera from the CT, the \u003Cstrong\u003Emusic volume in the flight scene is broken\u003C/strong\u003E. You can see this here in \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.twitch.tv/videos/123308728?t=01h37m41s\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ethis video\u003C/a\u003E. From then on, the music volume on the flight scene (not on the map scene) changes with the camera zoom. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot even going back to the KSP main menu is fixing this, one needs to fully restart KSP. Is there any chance to fix that?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRegarding the \u0022focus goes back to \u003Cstrong\u003Eroot part\u003C/strong\u003E instead of the \u003Cstrong\u003Ecenter of mass\u003C/strong\u003E\u0022-issue, I know, that the mod \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/zentarul/camerafocuschanger/tree/v1.0.1.0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ecamera focus changer\u003C/a\u003E is going back to the center of mass, so there one maybe can look, how it works.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe this is even related and fixed together. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-02-20T13:27:16Z\u0022 title=\u002202/20/2017 01:27  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 20, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Jebs_SY\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Stillkill","CreatedById":139336,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-02T05:30:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is all good and all, but can you update to 1.2 plz?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DoctorDavinci","CreatedById":150019,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-02T05:59:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222972619\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002284938\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221488432626\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139336\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Stillkill\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 minutes ago, Stillkill said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is all good and all, but can you update to 1.2 plz?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA member of the BDArmory team has taken it upon himself to maintain this mod in Baha\u0027s absence\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere is\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/130617-jrodriguez/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022130617\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/130617-jrodriguez/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@jrodriguez\u003C/a\u003E\u0027s github\u00A0releases\u00A0page\u00A0for\u00A0Camera\u00A0Tools:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/jrodrigv/CameraTools/releases\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/jrodrigv/CameraTools/releases\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBe advised that it was compiled for KSP v1.2.1, however I haven\u0027t noticed any issues running it in v1.2.2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI missed adding a link\u00A0to\u00A0this mod to the BDArmory Continued thread and will correct this in the near future ... in the meantime you can find other Baha mods that have been taken on by our team or other modders\u00A0in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E of the BDAc thread:\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/155014-122-bdarmory-continued-vessel-mover-vessel-switcher-bdmk22-destruction-effects-etc/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=2922016\u0026amp;embedComment=2922016\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Columbine","CreatedById":176395,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-31T22:33:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan somebody know if this mod will be operational for 1.2.2 very soon ? because i tried to make it work on this version but the keys are\u0027nt working at all..\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you !\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DoctorDavinci","CreatedById":150019,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-31T22:46:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223004924\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002284938\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221490999611\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176395\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Columbine\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 minutes ago, Columbine said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan somebody know if this mod will be operational for 1.2.2 very soon ? because i tried to make it work on this version but the keys are\u0027nt working at all..\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you !\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCamera Tools works fine in KSP v1.2.2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere will be a warning when starting up KSP that says CT is only for KSP v1.2.1 but you can ignore this as it works as is\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nukeboyt","CreatedById":68397,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-01T02:46:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI \u00A0would like to figure out how to \u00A0fly past an orbiting, rotating object \u00A0(like a rotating space station in orbit) without the camera rotating in unison with the station. \u00A0 Does anyone know if this is possible? \u00A0Thanks\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DoctorDavinci","CreatedById":150019,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-01T03:05:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223005170\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002284938\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221491014795\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002268397\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022nukeboyt\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 minutes ago, nukeboyt said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI \u00A0would like to figure out how to \u00A0fly past an orbiting, rotating object \u00A0(like a rotating space station in orbit) without the camera rotating in unison with the station. \u00A0 Does anyone know if this is possible? \u00A0Thanks\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:#272a34;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003ETargeting\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:#272a34;\u0022\u003E\n- Click \u0022Set target w/ click\u0022 then click on a vessel or part to set it as your target\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:#272a34;\u0022\u003E\n- You can also just click target self to target your active vessel\u0027s command unit\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:#272a34;\u0022\u003E\n- The camera will point at the target you select.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nukeboyt","CreatedById":68397,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-01T03:45:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223005192\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002284938\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221491015939\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150019\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DoctorDavinci\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n35 minutes ago, DoctorDavinci said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:#272a34;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003ETargeting\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:#272a34;\u0022\u003E\n- Click \u0022Set target w/ click\u0022 then click on a vessel or part to set it as your target\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:#272a34;\u0022\u003E\n- You can also just click target self to target your active vessel\u0027s command unit\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:#272a34;\u0022\u003E\n- The camera will point at the target you select.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks. \u00A0When I do this, the camera follows the target as it follows the prescribed path. \u00A0But the camera rotates in sync with the target as it\u00A0flies the path. \u00A0(The target is a rotating station). \u00A0\u00A0I\u0027d like to have the camera fly past the target but not rotate as it flies by.\u00A0 \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Columbine","CreatedById":176395,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-01T15:46:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223004939\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002284938\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221491000367\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150019\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DoctorDavinci\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 hours ago, DoctorDavinci said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCamera Tools works fine in KSP v1.2.2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere will be a warning when starting up KSP that says CT is only for KSP v1.2.1 but you can ignore this as it works as is\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut when i sintalled the mod on 1.2.2, the icon on the toolbar wasnt here and when i tried to open the mod with / on my keypad, the window was freeze on my right screen border...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DoctorDavinci","CreatedById":150019,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-01T16:42:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223005786\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002284938\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221491061572\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176395\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Columbine\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n57 minutes ago, Columbine said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut when i sintalled the mod on 1.2.2, the icon on the toolbar wasnt here and when i tried to open the mod with / on my keypad, the window was freeze on my right screen border...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo what I believe is happening is you are downloading from the link in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E of this thread\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease go to the following thread and download camera tools from there\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/155014-122-bdarmory-continued-vessel-mover-vessel-switcher-bdmk22-destruction-effects-etc/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis thread should be closed as it is old and Baha is no longer with us\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223005235\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002284938\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221491018309\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002268397\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022nukeboyt\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 hours ago, nukeboyt said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks. \u00A0When I do this, the camera follows the target as it follows the prescribed path. \u00A0But the camera rotates in sync with the target as it\u00A0flies the path. \u00A0(The target is a rotating station). \u00A0\u00A0I\u0027d like to have the camera fly past the target but not rotate as it flies by.\u00A0 \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStick a weapon manager on each of the craft, make one team B and then use the dogfight mode\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-04-01T16:44:26Z\u0022 title=\u002204/01/2017 04:44  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EApril 1, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by DoctorDavinci\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Columbine","CreatedById":176395,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-01T16:54:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you very much !\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jrodriguez","CreatedById":130617,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-02T17:16:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi all,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have released a new version of CameraTools compatible with KSP 1.2.9 and KSP 1.2.2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn this new version I have fixed the issue regarding when reverting cam was doing a wrong target to the root part.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/jrodrigv/CameraTools/releases/tag/v1.8.0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/jrodrigv/CameraTools/releases/tag/v1.8.0\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DiscoSlelge","CreatedById":114099,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-04T10:36:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m runing with the 1.2.2 but it seems to doesn\u0027t work, I install it in the game data (CameraTools folder unziped in the Game data) but there is nothing ingame, there is should be a little camera in the tool bar isn\u0027t it ? Btw I downloaded your latest version on github \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/130617-jrodriguez/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022130617\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/130617-jrodriguez/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@jrodriguez\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-04-04T10:37:35Z\u0022 title=\u002204/04/2017 10:37  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EApril 4, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by DiscoSlelge\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jebs_SY","CreatedById":169510,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-04T10:38:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223004939\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002284938\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221491000367\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150019\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DoctorDavinci\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 1.4.2017 at 0:46 AM, DoctorDavinci said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCamera Tools works fine in KSP v1.2.2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWorking fine? You don\u0027t have \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/84938-105-camera-tools-v151-dogfight-mode-autozoom-margin-slider-march-28/\u0026amp;page=11#comment-2961588\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ethis\u003C/a\u003E problem?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs soon as I use camera tools, the sound is broken. \u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#3498db;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe music volume raises/lowers when zooming in/out the ship\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E. Until one restarts KSP. For me, at least.\u003Cbr\u003E\nIs this a mod conflict, only I have?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-04-04T10:39:52Z\u0022 title=\u002204/04/2017 10:39  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EApril 4, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Jebs_SY\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jrodriguez","CreatedById":130617,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-04T11:02:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223008911\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002284938\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221491302213\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022114099\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DiscoSlelge\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n25 minutes ago, DiscoSlelge said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m runing with the 1.2.2 but it seems to doesn\u0027t work, I install it in the game data (CameraTools folder unziped in the Game data) but there is nothing ingame, there is should be a little camera in the tool bar isn\u0027t it ? Btw I downloaded your latest version on github \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/130617-jrodriguez/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022130617\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/130617-jrodriguez/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@jrodriguez\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan you check if you have a GameData folder inside your GameData folder?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DiscoSlelge","CreatedById":114099,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-04T13:02:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223008931\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002284938\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221491303779\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022130617\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jrodriguez\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, jrodriguez said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan you check if you have a GameData folder inside your GameData folder?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nChecked there\u0027s nothing I installed the folder Camera Tools normaly like other mods.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jrodriguez","CreatedById":130617,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-04T13:28:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223009012\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002284938\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221491310973\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022114099\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DiscoSlelge\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n23 minutes ago, DiscoSlelge said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nChecked there\u0027s nothing I installed the folder Camera Tools normaly like other mods.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWould you mind to report the issue on my repo the github section?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan you attach the logs? Thanks\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DiscoSlelge","CreatedById":114099,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-04T13:31:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223009027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002284938\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221491312492\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022130617\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jrodriguez\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, jrodriguez said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWould you mind to report the issue on my repo the github section?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan you attach the logs? Thanks\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo problemo I\u0027m at univeristy but once I get home I\u0027ll do it, can you explain me how to do ? I never did that before.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DoctorDavinci","CreatedById":150019,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-04T14:27:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223008912\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002284938\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221491302336\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022169510\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jebs_SY\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Jebs_SY said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWorking fine? You don\u0027t have \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/84938-105-camera-tools-v151-dogfight-mode-autozoom-margin-slider-march-28/\u0026amp;page=11#comment-2961588\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ethis\u003C/a\u003E problem?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs soon as I use camera tools, the sound is broken. \u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#3498db;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe music volume raises/lowers when zooming in/out the ship\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E. Until one restarts KSP. For me, at least.\u003Cbr\u003E\nIs this a mod conflict, only I have?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom what you describe it sounds like KSP is treating music like it treats craft sounds which is to say the further away from the craft you are the lower the sound effects will be ... The BDAc team will require your KSP.log, modlist and computer specs in order to get to the bottom of this as we aren\u0027t even able to confirm this is a mod conflict without this information\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jebs_SY","CreatedById":169510,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-04T14:46:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223009087\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002284938\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221491316038\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150019\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DoctorDavinci\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, DoctorDavinci said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom what you describe it sounds like KSP is treating music like it treats craft sounds which is to say the further away from the craft you are the lower the sound effects will be ... The BDAc team will require your KSP.log, modlist and computer specs in order to get to the bottom of this as we aren\u0027t even able to confirm this is a mod conflict without this information\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just tried it, it\u0027s easy to reproduce this error.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust removed ALL mods (/folders except Squad) and installed Camera\u00A0Tools 1.8.0 via \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E (which also installs Module Manager) on KSP 1.2.2.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith that \u0022vanilla\u002BCameraTools\u0022\u00A0install I was able to reproduce the \u0022\u003Cstrong\u003ECT breaks music volume\u003C/strong\u003E\u0022-problem easily. It\u0027s still there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#e74c3c;\u0022\u003ESee this \u003C/span\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://youtu.be/7e8oxurzUvY\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#e74c3c;\u0022\u003Evideo\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#e74c3c;\u0022\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-04-04T18:01:26Z\u0022 title=\u002204/04/2017 06:01  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EApril 4, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Jebs_SY\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}